.TH "drm_pci_alloc" 9 "drm_pci_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_pci_alloc \- Allocate a PCI consistent memory block, for DMA.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "drm_dma_handle_t *" drm_pci_alloc
.BI "(struct drm_device * dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t align "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "size" 12
size of block to allocate
.IP "align" 12
alignment of block
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
FIXME: This is a needless abstraction of the Linux dma-api and should be
removed.
.SH "RETURN"
A handle to the allocated memory block on success or NULL on
failure.
